>>Which of the following building blocks are you likely to find in a typical CNN architecture?<<

[x] A. Pooling layers {{ selected: A. True. Pooling layers are used for downsampling.}}
[x] B. Convolutional layers {{selected: B. True. Convolutional layers are the key component in Convolutional Neural Networks. }}
[x] C. Fully connected layers {{selected: C. True. CNNs will often be topped with MLPs and then a softmax to obtain a probability distribution that sums to 1. }}
